------------------------------------------------------
Introduction
------------------------------------------------------
Welcome!

This textmate bundle helps development of gezel2: http://rijndael.ece.vt.edu/gezel2/index.php/Main_Page code on a mac.

Currently supported:
* Code highlighting (nothing fancy yet)
* Simulation from textmate

------------------------------------------------------
Installation
------------------------------------------------------
You need to install the gezel simulator on you mac, see http://rijndael.ece.vt.edu/gezel2/index.php/GEZEL_Installation_Mac_OS_X

1. Download bundle (Press download in the top of this page)
2. Rename to: Gezel.tmbundle
3. Move the bundle into ~/Library/Application Support/TextMate/Bundles/ (~ is your home directory)
4. In textmate set these shell variables:

	* GZL_FDLSIM: The full path to the fdlsim program
	* GZL_CYCLES: Number of cycles to simulate. See gezel doc.
5. Open a gezel file (.fdl), verify it says Gezel in the bottom of textmate, and press Command-R to run a simulation of the file.

